File system has how to create foldeer, file, rename the file or folder, update.

The file system is a traditional way of storing data.
A few advantages of using a traditional way of storing are as follows:
1. Is universal
2. No need to learn any new language
3. Low maintenance cost

Disadvantages:
1. Lack of Security(Hacking may be easily happen)
2. Data inconsistency
3. Concurrent access not possible.


In File system, data can be stored within the machine. And not easy to access other. But in DB, data is
stored on online. Easily accessable.

Interview question:
Why we use DongoDB instead of using traditional file system?
In File system, data can be stored within the machine. And not easy to access other. But in DB, data is
stored on online. Easily accessable. 
